comment: Paul (LAC) clamps Noel's (PHI) arm and affects his ability to rebound.
Smith (PHI) maintains legal guarding position and does not affect Paul's (LAC) RSBQ.
Covington (PHI) makes contact to Jordan's (LAC) arm that affects his shot attempt.
Jordan (LAC) establishes a legal guarding position in Smith's (PHI) path, giving him room to avoid the off-ball screen.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that Redick (LAC) was behind the three-point line on his made field-goal attempt was upheld.
Okafor (PHI) maintains legal guarding position on Jordan's (LAC) alley-oop.
RATR shows that after Okafor (PHI) regains his dribble, Paul (LAC) makes contact with his arm/wrist in an attempt to strip the ball.
Okafor (PHI) moves his pivot foot as he starts his dribble.
Grant (PHI) maintains legal guarding position and does not affect the drive to the basket and shot attempt by Crawford (LAC).
Paul (LAC) maintains a legal guarding position as he defends Smith's (PHI) drive and shot attempt.
RHH shows Paul (LAC) makes contact with Smith (PHI) that affects his shot attempt.
LATR shows Johnson (LAC) maintains a legal guarding position on Smith's (PHI) drive, placing a legal bent forearm to Smith's side below the free throw line extended that does not affect his RSBQ.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that PHI be awarded possession was upheld.
Jordan (LAC) makes contact with Noel (PHI) as he gathers the ball to pass.
Jordan (LAC) does not maintain legal guarding position and makes contact to the body of Canaan (PHI) that affects his shot attempt.
Grant (PHI) makes contact with Jordan (LAC) as he receives the pass.
Grant (PHI) makes contact that impedes Redick (LAC) at the start of his dribble.
Noel (PHI) moves his pivot foot at the start of his dribble.
